# Workflow scripts MUST keep LF endings.
#
# The Workflow tool's approval layer refuses a script containing control characters
# ("script contains control characters that would be hidden in the approval"), and a CR is one.
# Measured 2026-07-21: three of eight invocation attempts for .claude/workflows/scout-summarize.js
# died on exactly that before the fan-out would launch.
#
# core.autocrlf is true on the machine this repo is developed on, so without this rule git
# restores CRLF on every checkout and the fix survives only in one working copy. The global
# normalize-postwrite hook already skips this directory; this is the other half.
.claude/workflows/*.js text eol=lf
